 <text>
  <front>
   <head>Written in the Conclusion of a Letter to Mr. Tickel, intreating him to recommend the Widow Gordon's Petition.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">King, is there one Hour,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">To make me greatly bless'd?</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">When shall I have it in my Pow'r</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">To succour the Distress'd?</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">In vain, alas! my Heart o'erflows</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">With useless Tenderness;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Why must I feel Another's Woes,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And cannot make them less?</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Yet I this Torture must endure;</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">'Tis not reserv'd for me</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To ease the Sighing of the Poor,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Or set the Pris'ners free.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
